When the user asks for a diagram, architecture overview, diff/PR review, plan review, dashboard, comparison table, slide deck, project recap, or any visual explanation, produce a **single self-contained HTML file** with the UltraExplainer skill rather than ASCII art or Markdown tables.

- Read `plugins/ultra-explainer/SKILL.md` and the relevant `plugins/ultra-explainer/references/*.md`.
- Start from the closest `plugins/ultra-explainer/templates/*.html`; inline `assets/aurora.css` + `assets/aurora.js` (escape literal `</script>` as `<\/script>`).
- Reason with the synthesis method (thesis-with-tension, evidence anchors, salience tiers T0≤3/T1≤7/T2-hidden, lowest-ink representation, first-viewport gate, self-audit).
- The Aurora system has light/dark + an optional glow toggle; keep glow budgeted and never draw structure not present in the source.
- Write the file and tell the user the path.
